ShCh-214 was a Shchuka-class submarine Shchuka-class submarine of the Soviet Navy. Her keel was laid down by 61 Kommunara in Nikolajev on 13 July 1935. She was launched on 23 April 1937 and commissioned on 4 March 1939 in the Black Sea Fleet.
Submarine was under command of Captain Vlasov Vladimir Yakovlevich until the loss of the vessel.cite web  author=Orlov Alex, Dmitriy Metelev, Evgeniy Chirva  url=http://www.town.ural.ru/ship/means/mens_v.php3#vlasov  title=  -    publisher=Town.ural.ru  date=  accessdate=2014-08-26
Loss
After having performed attacks in southern Black Sea, the submarine was employed as a transport unit to support the Soviet forces in the Siege of Sevastopol 194142 Siege of Sevastopol. During one of these mission, ShCh-214 was torpedoed in surface by the Italian motor torpedo boat MAS-571. 2 men of the crew survived.
Service history
Submarine scored some sinking in southern Black Sea, often against neutral Turkish schooners.
